    "{\n",
    " \"cells\": [\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# UBS Stock Return Analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"## Confidence Intervals, Statistical Testing & Market Scenarios\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Scientific Programming – Project Work FS2026**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"---\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Research Question\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Is the mean daily return of UBS stock significantly different from zero, and how do confidence interval widths vary across sample sizes and market regimes?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Objectives\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. Collect real-world UBS stock data via Yahoo Finance API\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. Compute confidence intervals for mean daily returns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. Perform hypothesis testing (t-test with p-value)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. Compare real data against synthetic market scenarios\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. Store results in an SQLite database\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 1. Setup & Imports\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"import numpy as np\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import pandas as pd\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import seaborn as sns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scipy import stats\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import re\\n\",\n",
    "    \"import sqlite3\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Project modules\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from analysis import (\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    ticker, log, make_reliability_table, summarize_returns_for_ci,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plot_reliability_table, build_ci_table, plot_mean_se_and_ci,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    plot_ci_widths, rolling_ci_analysis, plot_rolling_ci_all,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    t_confidence_interval, MeanCI\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from DataLoader import DataLoader, prepare_data\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from scenarios import generate_scenario, plot_scenarios_overview_one_image\\n\",\n",
    "    \"from database import (\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    get_connection, init_db, store_prices, store_ci_results,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    query_prices, query_ci_results, query_avg_return_by_ticker\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"sns.set_context(\\\"talk\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.rcParams.update({\\\"figure.dpi\\\": 120})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Analysing ticker: {ticker}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 2. Data Collection (Web API)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Using `yfinance` to fetch real-world stock data from Yahoo Finance.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Fetch ~6 months of daily data\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw = DataLoader(lookback_days=180).fetch()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Raw data shape: {raw.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"raw.head()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 3. Data Preparation\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Column name cleaning with **regular expressions**\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Forward-filling missing values\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Computing daily returns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**Data structures used**: lists, dictionaries, sets, tuples, pandas DataFrames\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Prepare 10 trading days for CI analysis\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stock10 = prepare_data(raw, n_trading_days=10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Prepared data shape: {stock10.shape}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(stock10)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Demonstrate Python built-in data structures\\n\",\n",
    "    \"price_list = stock10[\\\"Price\\\"].tolist()          # list\\n\",\n",
    "    \"return_tuple = tuple(stock10[\\\"Return\\\"].values)   # tuple\\n\",\n",
    "    \"date_set = set(stock10.index.date)               # set (unique dates)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stats_dict = {                                    # dictionary\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"mean_return\\\": stock10[\\\"Return\\\"].mean(),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"std_return\\\": stock10[\\\"Return\\\"].std(),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"min_price\\\": stock10[\\\"Price\\\"].min(),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"max_price\\\": stock10[\\\"Price\\\"].max(),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"n_unique_dates\\\": len(date_set)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\nSummary statistics (dict):\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"for k, v in stats_dict.items():\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    print(f\\\"  {k}: {v:.6f}\\\" if isinstance(v, float) else f\\\"  {k}: {v}\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 4. Data Exploration\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Tables and visualisations for exploratory analysis.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Full dataset for exploration\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stock_full = prepare_data(raw, n_trading_days=None)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Descriptive statistics table\\n\",\n",
    "    \"desc = stock_full.describe()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(desc)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Distribution plots\\n\",\n",
    "    \"fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 3, figsize=(16, 4))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Price time series\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].plot(stock_full.index, stock_full[\\\"Price\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_title(f\\\"{ticker} Price (last 6 months)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].set_ylabel(\\\"Price (CHF)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[0].grid(True, linestyle=\\\"--\\\", alpha=0.5)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Return distribution\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].hist(stock_full[\\\"Return\\\"], bins=30, edgecolor=\\\"black\\\", alpha=0.7)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].axvline(0, color=\\\"red\\\", linestyle=\\\"--\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_title(f\\\"{ticker} Return Distribution\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[1].set_xlabel(\\\"Daily Return\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# QQ plot\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stats.probplot(stock_full[\\\"Return\\\"].dropna(), dist=\\\"norm\\\", plot=axes[2])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"axes[2].set_title(\\\"Q-Q Plot (Normal)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.tight_layout()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plt.show()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 5. Reliability Table (Critical z-values)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"confs_table = [0.80, 0.90, 0.95, 0.98, 0.99, 0.998, 0.999]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"reliability_tbl = make_reliability_table(confs_table)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(reliability_tbl)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plot_reliability_table(reliability_tbl, title=\\\"Critical t-values (df=9)\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 6. Confidence Intervals (10 Trading Days)\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Compute mean, SE, df\\n\",\n",
    "    \"stats10 = summarize_returns_for_ci(stock10[\\\"Return\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Mean: {stats10.mean:.6f}, SE: {stats10.se:.6f}, df: {stats10.df}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Build CI table for multiple confidence levels\\n\",\n",
    "    \"ci_tbl = build_ci_table(stats10, [0.90, 0.95, 0.99])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(ci_tbl)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Visualise\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plot_mean_se_and_ci(stats10, ci_tbl, title_prefix=f\\\"{ticker} (10 days)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plot_ci_widths(ci_tbl, title=f\\\"{ticker} (10 days) – CI Widths\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 7. Statistical Hypothesis Test (p-value)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"**One-sample t-test**: Is the mean daily return significantly different from 0?\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $H_0$: $\\\\mu = 0$ (mean daily return is zero)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- $H_1$: $\\\\mu \\\\neq 0$ (mean daily return is non-zero)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Significance level: $\\\\alpha = 0.05$\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Test on 10-day sample\\n\",\n",
    "    \"t_stat_10, p_value_10 = stats.ttest_1samp(stock10[\\\"Return\\\"], popmean=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"ONE-SAMPLE T-TEST (10 trading days)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"t-statistic: {t_stat_10:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"p-value:     {p_value_10:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Result:      {'Reject H₀' if p_value_10 < 0.05 else 'Fail to reject H₀'} at α=0.05\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Test on full dataset (~6 months)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"t_stat_full, p_value_full = stats.ttest_1samp(stock_full[\\\"Return\\\"], popmean=0)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"ONE-SAMPLE T-TEST (full dataset, n={len(stock_full)})\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"t-statistic: {t_stat_full:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"p-value:     {p_value_full:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Result:      {'Reject H₀' if p_value_full < 0.05 else 'Fail to reject H₀'} at α=0.05\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Correlation analysis: returns vs. lagged returns\\n\",\n",
    "    \"returns = stock_full[\\\"Return\\\"].dropna()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"lagged = returns.shift(1).dropna()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"aligned = pd.DataFrame({\\\"r_t\\\": returns.iloc[1:].values, \\\"r_t_minus_1\\\": lagged.values})\\n\",\n",
    "    \"corr, corr_p = stats.pearsonr(aligned[\\\"r_t\\\"], aligned[\\\"r_t_minus_1\\\"])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"CORRELATION: r(t) vs r(t-1)\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"=\\\" * 50)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Pearson r:   {corr:.4f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"p-value:     {corr_p:.6f}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Result:      {'Significant' if corr_p < 0.05 else 'Not significant'} autocorrelation at α=0.05\\\")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 8. Rolling CI Analysis\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"confs = [0.90, 0.95, 0.99]\\n\",\n",
    "    \"roll_dfs = {c: rolling_ci_analysis(stock_full, window=10, conf=c) for c in confs}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plot_rolling_ci_all(roll_dfs, ystep=0.05, ylims=(-0.15, 0.20))\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 9. Synthetic Market Scenarios\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"stocks_60 = prepare_data(raw, n_trading_days=60)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"base_price = float(stocks_60[\\\"Price\\\"].iloc[0])\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"scenarios = {\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    f\\\"Real {ticker}\\\": stocks_60,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Bull\\\": generate_scenario(\\\"bull\\\", n_days=60, seed=42, base_price=base_price),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Bear\\\": generate_scenario(\\\"bear\\\", n_days=60, seed=42, base_price=base_price),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Volatile\\\": generate_scenario(\\\"volatile\\\", n_days=60, seed=42, base_price=base_price),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Crisis\\\": generate_scenario(\\\"crisis\\\", n_days=60, seed=42, base_price=base_price),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"Neutral\\\": generate_scenario(\\\"neutral\\\", n_days=60, seed=42, base_price=base_price),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"}\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"plot_scenarios_overview_one_image(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    scenarios, conf=[0.90, 0.95, 0.99], sample_n=10,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    title=f\\\"{ticker} Real Data vs. Synthetic Market Scenarios\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    rebase_to=base_price\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 10. SQLite Database Storage\\n\",\n",
    "    \"Storing data and results in an SQLite database and querying them back.\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"code\",\n",
    "   \"execution_count\": null,\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"outputs\": [],\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"# Store prices in database\\n\",\n",
    "    \"conn = get_connection()\\n\",\n",
    "    \"init_db(conn)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"n_stored = store_prices(stock_full, ticker, conn)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(f\\\"Stored {n_stored} price rows for {ticker}\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Store CI results\\n\",\n",
    "    \"store_ci_results(ci_tbl, ticker,\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                 window_start=str(stock10.index.min().date()),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                 window_end=str(stock10.index.max().date()),\\n\",\n",
    "    \"                 conn=conn)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"Stored CI results\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Query back\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n--- Queried prices (last 5) ---\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(query_prices(ticker, limit=5, conn=conn))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n--- Queried CI results ---\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(query_ci_results(ticker, conn=conn))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n--- Average return by ticker ---\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(query_avg_return_by_ticker(conn=conn))\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"# Direct SQL query example\\n\",\n",
    "    \"print(\\\"\\\\n--- Custom SQL: days with |return| > 3% ---\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"extreme_days = pd.read_sql_query(\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"SELECT date, price, return_ FROM stock_prices \\\"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    \\\"WHERE ticker = ? AND ABS(return_) > 0.03 ORDER BY ABS(return_) DESC\\\",\\n\",\n",
    "    \"    conn, params=(ticker,)\\n\",\n",
    "    \")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"display(extreme_days if len(extreme_days) > 0 else \\\"No days with |return| > 3%\\\")\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"conn.close()\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  },\n",
    "  {\n",
    "   \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "   \"metadata\": {},\n",
    "   \"source\": [\n",
    "    \"## 11. Conclusions\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Key Findings\\n\",\n",
    "    \"1. **Confidence intervals** widen with increasing confidence level — higher certainty requires wider intervals\\n\",\n",
    "    \"2. **Rolling analysis** reveals time-varying uncertainty in return estimates\\n\",\n",
    "    \"3. **Hypothesis test**: The p-value from the t-test indicates whether UBS daily returns are statistically different from zero\\n\",\n",
    "    \"4. **Autocorrelation**: Pearson correlation between consecutive returns tests for predictability\\n\",\n",
    "    \"5. **Scenario comparison**: Volatile/crisis scenarios produce wider CIs, reflecting greater estimation uncertainty\\n\",\n",
    "    \"\\n\",\n",
    "    \"### Methods Used\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Real-world data collection (yfinance Web API)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Data preparation with regex, pandas\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Python data structures: lists, dicts, sets, tuples, DataFrames\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Conditional statements, loops, procedural & OOP programming\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Statistical visualisations (matplotlib, seaborn)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- Statistical analysis with p-values (scipy)\\n\",\n",
    "    \"- SQLite database with SQL queries\"\n",
    "   ]\n",
    "  }\n",
    " ],\n",
